take a pull
Homonym Number:
Word Class: phrase
Sense Number:
Definition:to pull oneself together: often in imper.  stop!


Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: cf. P: `desist, discontinue': Aust: 20c: In imper. occasionally: Take a pull on oneself!
